# User Interface Roadmap

## Overview

Future development will focus on building a production-ready user interface that allows non-technical users to interact with the platform without requiring YAML or coding knowledge.

The goal is to create a streamlined creative workflow experience for internal marketing and design teams.

---

## Interface Technologies

Potential future UI technologies may include:
- Streamlit for rapid internal tooling
- React for scalable enterprise interfaces
- Component-based front-end systems
- Dashboard-driven workflows

The final implementation may vary depending on deployment needs and enterprise requirements.

---

## Campaign and Brand Input

Future interfaces may allow users to:
- Enter campaign details through forms
- Configure creative objectives
- Define brand guidelines
- Upload typography and logo assets
- Configure composition constraints
- Launch generation workflows visually

This would replace manual YAML editing for many workflows.

---

## Asset Upload and Processing

Future workflows may support uploading:
- Product photography
- Brand logos
- Reference imagery
- Existing campaign assets

The platform may automatically preprocess assets before composition.

Examples may include:
- Background removal
- Cropping adjustments
- Resolution enhancement
- Format normalization

---

## Adobe Integration Possibilities

Future integrations may allow the system to communicate with:
- Adobe Photoshop APIs
- Adobe Express
- Adobe Firefly
- Adobe Experience Manager (AEM)

For example:
- Uploaded product images with unwanted backgrounds could automatically be sent to Photoshop or Firefly for cleanup before returning to the composition pipeline.

---

## User Experience Goals

The long-term goal is to provide:
- Low-friction creative workflows
- Minimal technical overhead
- Fast iteration cycles
- Visual workflow transparency
- Better collaboration between creative and technical teams

The interface should allow internal teams to use advanced AI-driven workflows without requiring engineering expertise.
